                    text: "A worked example of a TEL schema: a \"contact\" record type.",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "Demonstrates the constructs an everyday schema author will reach for:",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "  - required and optional `field`s with `scalar` types",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "  - a `repeatable` field (`phone`)",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "  - a named `define`d struct (`phone-number`, `address`) referenced from",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "    multiple positions via `type`",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "  - a `select` member with all-`flag` variants for an enumerated status,",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "    which can be set inline as an atom on the parent compound",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "  - a `default` value on a required scalar",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "To see what a document conforming to this schema looks like, see the",
                },
                Comment {
                    text: "accompanying `contact-document.tel`. This schema document is itself",
                },
                Comment {
